  "prompt": "What should I do if my best friend's friend likes me but I like my best friend?",
  "response": "This is a delicate situation. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Be honest with yourself about your feelings\n- Are you sure you truly like your best friend romantically?\n- Are you willing to risk your friendship by pursuing a relationship?\n\n2. Communicate carefully\n- Don't lead on your best friend's other friend if you don't reciprocate their feelings\n- Be kind but clear about your lack of romantic interest\n\n3. Talk to your best friend\n- Be open about the situation\n- Ask for their advice and perspective\n- Ensure you're not creating unnecessary drama\n\n4. Consider the potential consequences\n- A romantic pursuit could complicate your friendship\n- Be prepared for potential awkwardness\n- Think about how this might affect your social group\n\n5. Give it time\n- Sometimes feelings change\n- Don't rush into anything\n- Focus on maintaining your existing friendships\n\n6. If you truly like your best friend\n- Consider carefully how to approach them\n- Be prepared that they might not feel the same way\n- Be ready to preserve the friendship if they don't reciprocate\n\nThe most important things are honesty, respect, and maintaining good relationships with everyone involved.",
